Rose Red Episode 1.
In 2001, Professor Reardon assembles a team of psychics to investigate the 
paranormal activities at Rose Red in Seattle. When they arrive at the house, 
strange things start to happen and the crew begins to find out some of the 
mysteries that surround it. Also, the back-stories of each of the psychics 
is introduced and particular attention is paid to the history of two 
characters, Emery Waterman and Annie Wheaton.

=>-Nancy Travis.
=>-Matt Ross.
=>-Julian Sands.

Director.
=>-Craig R Baxley.

Rose Red Episode 2.
While investigating the mansion, the team starts seeing disturbing visions 
and optical illusions. At night they have disturbing dreams and part of the 
group is visited by a ghost. This confirms to Joyce that Rose Red is still 
very much alive. But they carry on with the investigation. Also, Miller and 
Rimbauer have a strong argument, death starts to hit the house and the 
garden hides some mysterious secrets.

Stars.
=>-Nancy Travis.
=>-Matt Ross.
=>-Julian Sands.

Director.
=>-Craig R Baxley.

Rose Red Episode 3.
In this final episode, the team confronts the spirits that haunt the 
mansion. In an attempt to uncover the secret of Rose Red, Steven Rimbauer 
creates a telepathic link between Cathy and Annie, which leads to 
disastrous consequences. The mystery about what happened at Rose Red is 
finally revealed. However, the spectre of Ellen Rimbauer attacks the group 
and ghosts are all around them. Will the group be able to make it out of 
the mansion alive?
